  <section class="services" id="services">

    <h2 class="heading">Services</h2>
    
    
    <div class="services-container">
      <div class="service-box">
        <div class="service-info">
          <i class="bx bxl-figma"></i>
          <h4>UI / UX Design</h4>
          <p>Figma is a cloud-based design tool that humans operate through an intuitive, browser-accessible interface, allowing them to create, prototype, and collaborate on user interface designs in real time. 
            On the frontend, users interact with tools to draw, move, and style elements using clicks, drags, and keyboard shortcuts—everything happens visually on a digital canvas. 
            Behind the scenes, on the backend, Figma handles data storage, real-time collaboration, and synchronization, ensuring that every change made by one user is instantly reflected for others. </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-box">
        <div class="service-info">
          <i class="bx bx-code"></i>
          <h4>Frontend Development</h4>
          <p>The frontend is the part of a digital system that humans directly interact with—like websites, apps, or software interfaces. 
            It includes everything users see and click on, such as buttons, menus, forms, and images. 
            Tools like HTML, CSS, and JavaScript build these experiences, and frontend developers focus on making the interface intuitive, responsive, and accessible to ensure smooth and enjoyable interaction for users.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-box">
        <div class="service-info">
          <i class="bx bx-code-curly"></i>
          <h4>Backend Develompent</h4>
          <p>The backend is the part of a system that humans don't see—it powers everything behind the scenes. 
            Backend operation involves managing data, handling logic, and ensuring the system functions correctly in response to user requests. 
            Humans interact with the backend indirectly through frontend interfaces; for instance, when a user logs in or retrieves information, the backend processes that request through servers, databases, and APIs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

